    <comment type="function">
      <text evidence="5">Catalyzes the initial cyclization step in the biosynthesis of ginkgolides, a structurally unique family of diterpenoids that are highly specific platelet-activating-factor receptor antagonists. Bifunctional enzyme that catalyzes two sequential cyclizations of geranylgeranyl diphosphate (GGPP) to levopimaradiene.</text>
    </comment>
    <comment type="catalytic activity">
      <reaction>
        <text>(2E,6E,10E)-geranylgeranyl diphosphate = (+)-copalyl diphosphate</text>
        <dbReference id="RHEA:24316" type="Rhea"/>
        <dbReference id="CHEBI:58635" type="ChEBI"/>
        <dbReference id="CHEBI:58756" type="ChEBI"/>
        <dbReference id="5.5.1.12" type="EC"/>
      </reaction>
    </comment>
    <comment type="catalytic activity">
